      "caseNotesList": [],
      "storyOfPersecution": "\"Yes, my family and I have been threatened and persecuted in my country by a criminal gang that operates from a Colombian prison and calls themselves \"Negro Over\" in Colombia. My partner Zuly Ester Iglesia was an administrator in a company and had a good position and at the end of 2003 she began to receive harassment through phone calls and they threatened her so that she would pay them money. She filed a complaint because they stole all the money from our bank account and those people told her that they knew everything about us. Their boss was also extorted by the same people and the police did nothing to protect us. And that scared us a lot, because that gang killed people who did not agree to the extortion. We fear for our lives and we run away. This is a short summary of my claim that I prepared at a pro-se clinic: I may supplement it at a later date.\" I589 p 1Yes, I am very afraid to return because the people who threatened us are very dangerous and carry out murders and kidnappings from prison. In Colombia the police and the government do not protect me and my life and that of my family are in danger.\nThis is a short summary of my claim that I prepared at a pro-se clinic: I may supplement it at a later date. (I589 p 6)",
